milestones.description: David Boon and Geoff Marsh's 212-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 182 between Rick McCosker and Alan Turner
David Boon and Geoff Marsh's 212-run partnership is the highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 193 between Graham Gooch and Bill Athey
This is the highest match aggregate (501) involving teams Australia & India in ODIs
McDermott has conceded the most runs in an innings (75) in ODIs for AUS, going past David Colley's record of 72
